title: Three top Ankara police officials sacked after bombings - Region - World
text:
Related Turkey faces period of instability in wake of attacks ISIS prime suspect in Ankara bombing: Turkey PM Turkey sees ISIS hand in Ankara bombings: Security Sources Three senior Ankara police officials have been axed over Saturday's twin bombings at a peace rally in the Turkish capital which killed 97, the interior ministry said Wednesday.
The three include the chief of police for Ankara province and his intelligence and public security heads, a statement said, cited by Turkish media.
